gui_attach_to_cursor(25.10)                        gui_attach_to_cursor(25.10)

Name
       gui_attach_to_cursor  -  Attaches  selected or specified objects to the
       cursor

Syntax
       gui_attach_to_cursor

       [-help]

       [ -selected  | <objects> ]

       Attaches selected or specified objects to the cursor. The use model  is
       as follows:

              * Select  the  object(s)  to  be  moved  by  using  the  gui_at-
                tach_to_cursor command.

              * Zoom into the location where you want to place the object(s).

              * Click at the required location to place the selected object(s)
                there.

       This command is useful during floorplanning when you may need  to  move
       multiple objects into the same zoomed in area.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the gui_attach_to_cursor command.

              For  a detailed description of the command, use the man command:
              man gui_attach_to_cursor.

       <objects>
              Specifies the object pointer list.

       -selected
              Attaches the selected objects to the cursor.

Example
       The following command attaches objects A and B to the cursor:

       gui_attach_to_cursor {A B}

       Now, move the cursor to the layout and click at the desired location to
       place objects A and B there.

Related Information
              * gui_select

              * zoomIn

              * zoomOut

              * zoomTo

